Dual-channel DDR is the must-have memory-controller design among performance
PC chipsets, so SiS' newest Pentium 4 platform boasts dual DDR333 support.
But has Intel's move to Hyper-Threading and, soon, an 800MHz system bus
spoiled SiS' product planning?

