Latest News and Analysis
------------------------

E.G. for Example: Your Next PC? You Won't Recognize It
Pundits (including HwC's editor) have pontificated about notebooks replacing
desktop PCs, but while sales trends point that way, they're not moving that
quickly. That's given desktops time to strike back -- and what's the trend
that ties the newest corporate office systems, Shuttle's high-performance
cubes, and Sony's Vaio W coffee-table conversation piece? Let's get small.
(http://www.hardwarecentral.com/hardwarecentral/editorials/4611/1/)

Maxtor, Iomega, SmartDisk Expand External Hard Disk Choices
Whether you're looking for a pocket-size 60GB drive or a desktop-swift 200GB
model with one-button backup, new portable hard disks from SmartDisk,
Iomega, and Maxtor offer a variety of FireWire- and USB 2.0-based storage
and file-sharing options.
(http://www.hardwarecentral.com/hardwarecentral/news/4613/1/)

Microsoft Introduces Windows Media 9, Updated Player and Movie Maker
New versions of Windows XP's Media Player and Movie Maker (free) and a
party-jukebox Plus pack ($20) are just part of Microsoft's new plan to set
the standard for high-quality streaming audio and video: The software
giant's licensing its copy-protection-friendly technologies at half the cost
of rivals such as MPEG-4.
(http://www.hardwarecentral.com/hardwarecentral/news/4614/1/)

